        <content type="html" xml:base="https://trix.is-a.dev/blog/website-rewrite-in-zola/">&lt;h1 id=&quot;backstory&quot;&gt;Backstory&lt;&#x2F;h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Who dosent need a website? so a year ago I thought I‚Äôd create a website for myself, and I did. But guess what? it was in pure HTML and CSS (prolly from some github) repo.
But i really felt a need to have a better looking website, in which i could showcase my projects, and maybe even write a blog.&lt;&#x2F;p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;So a frnd of mine &lt;a class=&quot;external&quot; href=&quot;https:&#x2F;&#x2F;gasparvardanyan.github.io&#x2F;&quot;&gt;Gasper&lt;&#x2F;a&gt;&lt;small&gt;(a very cool guy)&lt;&#x2F;small&gt; suggested me to use &lt;a class=&quot;external&quot; href=&quot;https:&#x2F;&#x2F;gohugo.io&#x2F;&quot;&gt;Hugo&lt;&#x2F;a&gt; and i was like ‚Äúwts hugo?‚Äù.
I did watched a pretty good,crisp and short video on how to use it and i was like ‚Äúokay, i‚Äôll give it a try‚Äù.&lt;&#x2F;p&gt;
